HEADWORD: Pseudo-peripteral
<hw>Pseu`do-pe*rip"ter*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pseudo-</ets> + <ets>peripteral</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pseudop⟦eacute⟧ript⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>Falsely or imperfectly peripteral, as a temple having the columns
at the sides attached to the walls, and an ambulatory only at the ends
or only at one end.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
pseudo-peripteral temple.</def> <rj><au>Oxf. Gloss.</au></rj>
